================================================================================
                      THERMAL ANALYSIS
================================================================================

Thermal Characteristics:
  Die Size: 25.2 mm²
  Package: BG400 (23×23mm)
  Thermal Resistance (JA): 78°C/W

Temperature Calculation (Ambient: 25°C):
  Power Dissipation:    42.3 mW = 0.0423 W
  ΔT = 0.0423 W × 78°C/W = 3.3°C
  Junction Temperature: 25°C + 3.3°C = 28.3°C
  Thermal Margin: 56.7°C (excellent)

Thermal Stress:
  DSP Block Hot Spot: ~29°C (highest)
  LUT Array: ~27°C
  Thermal Gradient: <2°C across die

Temperature Sensitivity:
  At 85°C ambient:
    Junction Temp: 88.3°C (exceeds limit)
    Recommendation: Add airflow or passive cooling

  At 55°C ambient:
    Junction Temp: 58.3°C (safe with margin)
    Recommendation: Normal operation

Thermal Management:
  - No heat sink required for <50°C ambient
  - Consider thermal vias under DSP blocks
  - PCB airflow recommended for >50°C ambient
  - Thermal interface material not required

================================================================================
                      POWER OPTIMIZATION OPPORTUNITIES
================================================================================

Current Efficiency: 96% (good utilization)

Potential Optimizations:

  1. Power Gating (Potential Savings: 5.2 mW)
     - Gate unused DSP blocks (2 blocks × 1.275 mW)
     - Gate clock to DSP when not processing
     - Implementation difficulty: Moderate

  2. Supply Voltage Scaling (Potential Savings: 3.8 mW)
     - Reduce core voltage from 1.0V to 0.9V
     - Speed penalty: ~15% reduction in Fmax
     - Status: Not recommended (margin is tight)

  3. Clock Gating (Potential Savings: 0.8 mW)
     - Disable input sampling when no data available
     - Status: Could implement with valid_in signal

  4. Reduce Frequency (Potential Savings: 7.1 mW)
     - Operate at 50 MHz instead of 100 MHz
     - Throughput reduced by 50%
     - Status: Not recommended unless throughput not critical

Total Optimization Potential: 9.2 mW (21.8% reduction)
Current Design: Power-optimal for specified throughput

